Those who started the vaccine last year or earlier, have to cover other doses of the vaccine as well.
The first dose of the vaccine must be received between the third and fifth month of age.
Last year, a quarter of families voluntarily let their children vaccinate against pneumococcals.
Parents however paid for a dose of 1600 crowns and more.
To vaccinate younger children, four doses are needed.
Experts generally estimate that insurance companies will spend 300 to 450,000 crowns per year on vaccines.
